COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION AND WORKFORCE,
DEVELOPMENT
BILL NO. 36-0133
Thirty-Sixth Legislature of the Virgin Islands
August 26, 2025
An act amending title 17 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 10, section 111(a)(1) providing mental
health education and instruction
PROPOSED BY: Senator Milton E. Potter
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 17 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 10, section 111, subsection (a)(1) is
3 amended by striking “and” and by adding the following after “environment”:
4 “,and mental health education and instruction that includes age-appropriate model
5 learning activities for grades kindergarten through 12 on the overarching mental health
6 themes like early intervention and prevention, stigma and discrimination reduction and
7 holistic approach to well-being and core principles such as person-centered care, ethical
8 practice and empowerment.. The mental health education shall include learning activities
9 that develop pupils’ mental health wellness, social connectedness and supportive
10 relationships through resiliency, problem solving skills, coping skills, self-esteem, and a
11 positive school and home environment. Mental health education shall also include
12 learning activities that encompass the mental health components of the National Health
13 Education Standards.”
14 BILL SUMMARY
15 The bill adds mental health education to the school health programs.
